The paper deals with signal detection in MIMO systems, which is a topic related to information theory (cs.IT). The use of Markov chain Monte Carlo (MCMC) techniques for solving integer least-squares (ILS) problems is a common approach in machine learning (cs.LG) and statistical inference (cs.SI). The paper also discusses the mixing time of the MCMC detector, which is a topic related to computational complexity and algorithms (cs.DS). Finally, the paper proposes an optimized algorithm for solving ILS problems, which is a topic related to numerical analysis (cs.NA).
